The paper deals with planar straight-line drawings of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of edge length ratio is related to graph theory and combinatorics (cs.DM), and the paper specifically studies 2-trees, which is a type of data structure in computer science (cs.DS). The paper also involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses a procedure for generating drawings with a specific ratio, which could be considered a topic in simulation and modeling (cs.SI).
